      "id": "a12017b878753bd9",
      "text": "Teachers are busy. Teachers are motivated, but the framework is ‘another thing’. \n\nAllowing them to choose how big or how small critical for gaining momentum. Allowing them to prescribe their own experiment. Could decide how much time, the parts they felt were particularly relevant. \n\nOne example: one teacher felt that sharing voice was limited so she started focusing there. \n\nAllowing teachers to be in the drivers seat, given the needs of their students rather than being dictated by leadership. \n\nSeeing multiple ways, each mode of experiment brings something different. Also learning a lot from the variety of experiments, failures from one might be an opportunity in another. \n\nNo one size fits all, can be deeply personalize to each class depending how courageous the teacher is at the time. \n"
    }
